If you want to keep using JUnit 4 (like mentioned in the question), check your Gradle build file for any `useJUnitPlatform()` and remove it. 

Instead your test block should look like this:

     test {
         useJUnit()  // JUnit 4
         
         // ... other config ...
     }

With this you still can use JUnit 4 in legacy projects via Gradle without the need of upgrading to JUnit 5.

